                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="iv(erso)" facs="002"> f.iv(erso), left</locus><desc>Crude drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="iv(erso)" facs="002"> f.iv(erso), right</locus><desc><ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/> <name ref="PRS4306GabraMa"/> surrounded by creatures and bird. With caption <q>“David and Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus.” </q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#5r" facs="007"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#46r" facs="048"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/>,<persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> and the <term key="dragon"/> with caption <q>“Saint George and Berutawit.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#84v" facs="087"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/> with captions (l. to r.) <q>“Maryam,” “Langinos,” [with one eye closed] “Saint John,” and “Jew.”</q> A caption on the top of the <term key="cross"/> gives the initials for the phrase, <q>“Jesus of Nazareth, King of the Jews.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#104r" facs="106"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp ="AT1049Resurrection"/> raising <persName ref="PRS1386Adam"/> and <persName ref="PRS3926Eve"/>. Two evil men below (showing one eye) remain in the ground. With caption <q>“with our father, Adam,” “How Our Lord Jesus Christ was raised from the dead on the third day,” “with our mother, Eve,” “Jew,” and “Jew.” </q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#150r" facs="152"/><desc><ref type ="authFile" corresp="AT1062CoronationMary"/> surrounded by members of the Holy Trinity. With caption <q>“How the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit enthroned Saint Mary.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#204v" facs="207"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/> and the three young men in the furnace. With captions (l. to r.) <q>“the three children,” “Saint Michael,” and “How he rescued the three children.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#208v" facs="211"/><desc>Crude, colored drawing of <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/></desc></decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d10">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #20r" facs="003 023"/> (ornate ḥaräg in black ink);
                      <locus target="#10r" facs="012"/> (dotted line of small black inked crescents);
                      <locus target="#30v" facs="033"/> (variegated black and vellum boxes separating bodies of text);
                      <locus target="#43r #151v" facs="045 #154"/> (black, white, red, and brown ornate ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#52v #60v" facs="055 063"/> (line of alternating black and red dots with reticular woven pattern drawn above it);
                      <locus target="#60r #103v #138v #143v #160r #177r #184v #206v" facs="062 106 141 146 162 179 187 209"/> (multiple full stops between two red and black alternating dotted lines);
                      <locus target="#71v" facs="074"/> (line of alternating red and black dots with multiple full stops above it);
                      <locus target="#85r #95v #120v #186v #190r #201r" facs="087 098 123 189 192 203"/> (line of alternating black and red dots)
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
